President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his Administration. Maria E. Brewer of Indiana has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Sierra Leone. James Byrne of Virginia has been nominated to be General Counsel of the Department of Veterans Affairs. Gerald W. Fauth of Virginia has been nominated to be a Member of the National Mediation Board. Jamie McCourt of California has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Belgium. Robert Wood Johnson IV has been nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the United Kingdom. Michael Rigas of Massachusetts has been nominated to be Deputy Director of the Office of Personnel Management.